00:56.566 --> 00:58.283
Hello?

00:58.318 --> 01:01.370
Hi, honey. It's me.

01:01.405 --> 01:03.407
I went to see the doctor today,

01:03.907 --> 01:06.410
'Cause ever since you've been gone,

01:06.445 --> 01:09.878
I had a pain deep down inside.

01:09.913 --> 01:12.916
He says there's nothing
really wrong with me.

01:12.951 --> 01:15.436
I'm just missin' my man.

01:15.471 --> 01:17.886
So, honey, please...

01:17.921 --> 01:20.924
come on home as soon as you can.

01:20.959 --> 01:23.444
♪♪ Doctor's orders ♪♪

01:23.479 --> 01:25.938
♪♪ Say there's only ♪♪

01:25.973 --> 01:28.937
♪♪ One thing for me ♪♪

01:28.972 --> 01:31.867
♪♪ Nothing he can do ♪♪

01:31.902 --> 01:36.573
♪♪ 'Cause only you can cure me ♪♪

01:38.075 --> 01:39.576
I heard you have a much better chance

01:39.611 --> 01:41.043
Of getting in if you come by cab.

01:41.078 --> 01:43.080
You're really worried about getting in?

01:43.115 --> 01:44.046
Yes.

01:44.081 --> 01:46.083
I thought you'd been
here several times before.

01:46.118 --> 01:47.049
Not the front way.

01:47.084 --> 01:48.085
They were private parties.

01:48.120 --> 01:49.051
We came in the back.

01:49.086 --> 01:51.521
We look really good tonight.

01:51.556 --> 01:53.957
I'm sure we're going to get in.

01:57.594 --> 01:59.596
Get back.

02:01.098 --> 02:03.350
Let's get a cab.

02:03.385 --> 02:05.567
Maybe you're right.

02:05.602 --> 02:08.104
When we get out, don't
stop where the crowd is.

02:08.139 --> 02:09.071
Just follow me right in.

02:09.106 --> 02:10.607
When we get out, we just follow you in.

02:11.108 --> 02:11.608
Yeah.

02:12.058 --> 02:14.611
Why don't you put this on?

02:14.646 --> 02:16.113
What?

02:16.613 --> 02:18.064
Just until we get inside.

02:18.148 --> 02:19.616
I don't get it.

02:37.134 --> 02:39.636
We're all together.

02:41.138 --> 02:42.053
Van!

02:42.088 --> 02:43.605
Only him.

02:43.640 --> 02:46.643
We're together. Come on, van.

02:46.678 --> 02:48.412
This is important.

02:48.447 --> 02:50.112
These are my friends.

02:50.147 --> 02:52.899
You can go in, but they'll have to wait.

02:54.151 --> 02:56.603
Hey, nice coat.

03:04.161 --> 03:06.163
Don't worry, Jimmy. We don't care.

03:06.198 --> 03:07.164
I can't believe it.

03:07.664 --> 03:09.131
Yeah, what an asshole.

03:09.166 --> 03:10.167
You know, that had nothing to do

03:10.202 --> 03:11.133
With you guys.

03:11.168 --> 03:12.669
Van just wanted to put me in my place.

03:13.170 --> 03:14.171
Apparently, it happens all the time.

03:14.206 --> 03:15.137
Jerk.

03:15.172 --> 03:16.673
It's happened to you before?

03:16.708 --> 03:18.675
No, but it was overdue.

03:19.176 --> 03:20.677
You know, none of us
really wanted to go anyway.

03:20.712 --> 03:22.196
Yeah, we're exhausted.

03:22.231 --> 03:23.680
No, I really wanted to go.

03:28.185 --> 03:30.152
There's Jimmy Steinway.

03:30.187 --> 03:31.688
I can't believe it...
He's already leaving?

03:31.723 --> 03:34.156
You like him?

03:34.191 --> 03:36.193
I could never be interested in anyone

03:36.228 --> 03:37.694
Who worked in advertising.

03:39.196 --> 03:41.163
God. You were right.

03:41.198 --> 03:45.202
This place has gotten
really hard to get into.

03:52.209 --> 03:54.211
Who's the other guy
you were interested in?

04:07.224 --> 04:09.476
♪♪ Doctor's orders ♪♪

04:09.511 --> 04:12.121
♪♪ Say there's only ♪♪

04:12.156 --> 04:14.695
♪♪ One thing for me ♪♪

04:14.730 --> 04:17.199
Phew. Oh, god. We made it.

04:17.233 --> 04:18.735
This is the last time I'm coming here.

04:18.769 --> 04:20.237
I always want to be able to say,

04:20.272 --> 04:21.505
"I got into the club."

04:21.540 --> 04:22.739
Of course we got in.

04:23.240 --> 04:25.242
Who was the second guy
you were interested in?

04:25.277 --> 04:26.208
Tom Platt.

04:26.243 --> 04:28.245
Oh, well, that's a lot better.

04:28.745 --> 04:29.246
How do you mean?

04:29.746 --> 04:31.998
Well, Tom Platt's
smart and somewhat cool,

04:32.033 --> 04:34.251
A lawyer involved in
environmental causes...

04:34.286 --> 04:37.254
Not to mention tall, dark, and handsome.

04:37.289 --> 04:40.222
♪♪ Emotion every day ♪♪

04:40.257 --> 04:44.261
♪♪ A lovin' spoonful to be taken ♪♪

04:44.296 --> 04:48.230
♪♪ It's the only thing ♪♪

04:48.265 --> 04:51.268
♪♪ Stoppin' this empty heart of mine ♪♪

04:51.303 --> 04:53.287
♪♪ From breakin' ♪♪

04:53.322 --> 04:54.797
♪♪ Won't get better ♪♪

04:54.832 --> 04:56.273
♪♪ Till you're back ♪♪

04:56.773 --> 04:59.776
Nina!
Please... Stop!

04:59.811 --> 05:02.279
Nina!

05:06.783 --> 05:07.284
Nina!

05:08.785 --> 05:11.288
Please... stop.

05:12.289 --> 05:13.790
Hey, Mcgrath!

05:14.291 --> 05:15.792
Come back here!

05:19.796 --> 05:21.798
It's not what you think.

05:21.833 --> 05:23.765
I'm...

05:23.800 --> 05:25.302
I think I'm gay.

05:25.337 --> 05:28.770
What?

05:28.805 --> 05:30.807
That's not possible.

05:32.809 --> 05:33.775
How?

05:33.810 --> 05:35.277
It's always been there, I guess.

05:35.312 --> 05:37.314
I've only begun to acknowledge it now.

05:37.349 --> 05:40.817
You really think you're gay?

05:40.852 --> 05:41.783
Taxi.

05:41.818 --> 05:43.320
I was just starting law school

05:43.355 --> 05:44.286
When the first up-Tempo

05:44.321 --> 05:45.822
Philadelphia international hits broke:

05:45.857 --> 05:47.324
Some people don't
consider that disco...

05:47.359 --> 05:48.325
Because
it's good...

05:48.825 --> 05:51.828
But I remember feeling
absolutely electrified.

05:51.863 --> 05:53.097
You feel electrified often.

05:53.132 --> 05:54.331
No, but this was different.

05:54.831 --> 05:55.797
I loved the idea that there'd be

05:55.832 --> 05:57.334
All these great places
for people to go dancing,

05:57.369 --> 05:59.336
After the terrible social wasteland

05:59.371 --> 06:01.105
Of our college years. Uhff.

06:01.140 --> 06:03.741
You've been to a lot of discos?

06:03.776 --> 06:05.810
No. In fact, practically none.

06:05.845 --> 06:07.809
For me, law school wasn't easy,

06:07.844 --> 06:09.346
And I haven't had much of a social life

06:09.381 --> 06:10.812
Since coming to the city, either.

06:10.847 --> 06:13.350
But I still consider
myself a loyal adherent

06:13.385 --> 06:14.368
To the disco movement.

06:14.403 --> 06:15.352
It's a "movement"?

06:15.387 --> 06:16.353
Sort of.

06:16.603 --> 06:17.854
What I found terribly encouraging

06:18.355 --> 06:19.856
Was the idea that when
the time in life came

06:20.357 --> 06:20.857
To have a social life,

06:21.358 --> 06:22.859
There'd be all these great places

06:22.894 --> 06:23.825
For people to go to,

06:23.860 --> 06:25.111
Because, as you'll remember,

06:25.146 --> 06:26.363
For many years, there were none.

06:26.398 --> 06:27.329
Yeah.

06:27.364 --> 06:28.830
What I didn't realize...

06:28.865 --> 06:31.368
is that it gets so
impossible to get into.

06:31.403 --> 06:33.387
Let's call it a night.

06:33.422 --> 06:35.372
No, wait. I have an idea.

06:35.407 --> 06:36.838
Jimmy.

06:36.873 --> 06:38.875
Here take this. Jimmy!

06:38.910 --> 06:41.378
Take this. Jimmy!

06:44.881 --> 06:45.882
Oh, hi.

06:45.917 --> 06:46.848
Hi.

06:46.883 --> 06:47.884
You're des's friend.

06:47.919 --> 06:49.386
Yeah, hi.

06:52.389 --> 06:54.391
Where are Marshall and Steve?

06:54.426 --> 06:56.393
They've gone back to the hotel.

06:56.428 --> 06:57.894
Jim, come on.

06:58.395 --> 06:58.895
I can't believe it.

06:59.396 --> 07:00.730
Jim, let's go.

07:03.399 --> 07:05.401
They wanted me to apologize for them.

07:05.436 --> 07:06.402
They were really bushed.

07:06.437 --> 07:07.403
What a disaster.

07:07.903 --> 07:08.869
No.

07:08.904 --> 07:10.906
I can't believe it.

07:10.941 --> 07:12.408
Wow!

07:13.409 --> 07:14.375
♪♪ Your body ♪♪

07:14.410 --> 07:16.412
♪♪ Your body, my body ♪♪

07:16.447 --> 07:18.431
♪♪ Everybody ♪♪

07:18.466 --> 07:20.381
♪♪ With nobody ♪♪

07:20.416 --> 07:21.917
Do you like nightmares?

07:21.952 --> 07:22.918
No.

07:23.419 --> 07:24.885
Well, I do.

07:24.920 --> 07:26.887
It's not obviously connected, but...

07:26.922 --> 07:28.924
I think that's what made
me a little more tolerant

07:28.959 --> 07:30.426
Of the guys at Hampshire.

07:30.461 --> 07:32.393
What do you mean?

07:32.428 --> 07:34.395
You were a bit critical.

07:34.430 --> 07:36.432
The guys there preferred
women more..."laid-Back."

07:36.932 --> 07:38.899
I'm laid-Back.

07:38.934 --> 07:40.901
For whatever reason,

07:40.936 --> 07:42.938
You didn't have much
of a social life there.

07:42.973 --> 07:44.905
I had a
social life...

07:44.940 --> 07:46.942
Just not one of those
terrible pretend-Marriages.

07:46.977 --> 07:48.444
The Hampshire guys were jerks,

07:48.944 --> 07:50.946
Hippy-Dippy suburbanites
with all this hair...

07:50.981 --> 07:53.216
And extremely dim
intellectual interests.

07:53.251 --> 07:55.451
I'm sorry, I don't
consider the guy who did

07:55.486 --> 07:56.952
The Spiderman comics a serious writer.

07:56.987 --> 07:58.419
Alice, one thing I've noticed

07:58.454 --> 07:59.955
Is that people hate being criticized.

08:00.456 --> 08:01.922
Everyone hates that.

08:01.957 --> 08:03.959
It's one of the great
truths of human nature.

08:04.460 --> 08:06.927
I think it's why my
parents got divorced.

08:06.962 --> 08:08.964
I'm sorry... It's just
that you're so terrific...

08:09.465 --> 08:10.466
It makes me sick to think
that you might get in

08:10.966 --> 08:12.217
That terrible situation again,

08:12.252 --> 08:13.469
Where everyone
hated you...

08:13.504 --> 08:14.935
Hated me?

08:14.970 --> 08:17.438
You're wonderful.

08:17.473 --> 08:20.976
Maybe, in physical terms,
I'm a little cuter than you,

08:21.011 --> 08:23.479
But you should be much
more popular than I am...

08:23.514 --> 08:24.945
it would be such a shame

08:24.980 --> 08:26.982
If what happened in
college repeated itself.

08:27.017 --> 08:29.485
Why would it repeat itself?

08:29.985 --> 08:31.452
You're right.

08:31.487 --> 08:32.453
I just think it's so important

08:32.488 --> 08:34.990
To be in control of
your own destiny...

08:35.025 --> 08:37.457
Not to fall into that fifties cliche

08:37.493 --> 08:39.495
Of waiting by the
phone for guys to call:

08:39.530 --> 08:40.496
The right ones never do.

08:40.996 --> 08:41.962
Those who do,

08:41.996 --> 08:43.999
You have to make the most
ridiculous excuses to:

08:44.034 --> 08:46.001
The nice ones get hurt
feelings and hate you;

08:46.036 --> 08:47.503
The jerks inevitably corner you

08:47.538 --> 08:49.004
Into going out anyway.

08:49.505 --> 08:50.471
Late at night you find yourself

08:50.506 --> 08:52.508
With some awful guy
with disgusting breath,

08:52.543 --> 08:53.776
Thrusting his belly up against you,

08:53.811 --> 08:55.010
Trying to stick his slobbering tongue

08:55.511 --> 08:56.977
In your mouth. Ugh, yecch.

08:57.012 --> 08:59.515
Thank god this is a
whole new era in music

08:59.550 --> 09:01.517
And social models!

09:03.519 --> 09:06.522
We're in complete control.

09:06.557 --> 09:08.023
Look down.

09:08.524 --> 09:09.525
There are a lot of choices out there.

09:10.025 --> 09:12.493
♪♪ One night in a disco ♪♪

09:12.528 --> 09:14.279
♪♪ On the outskirts of frisco ♪♪

09:14.314 --> 09:15.673
Fantastic. This place is better

09:15.708 --> 09:17.032
Than I could have imagined.

09:17.533 --> 09:18.534
It's too bad Steve and
Marshall didn't come...

09:18.569 --> 09:21.304
They really would have loved this.

09:21.339 --> 09:24.039
Don't worry about it. So what.

09:24.074 --> 09:25.005
It's so stupid.

09:25.040 --> 09:26.541
I'm sure it's Jimmy.

09:26.576 --> 09:28.043
I think it's much better to wait

09:28.544 --> 09:29.545
Until things happen naturally.

09:30.045 --> 09:31.547
Forcing things never works.

09:31.582 --> 09:32.513
That's not true.

09:32.548 --> 09:35.050
Forcing things usually
works beautifully.

09:35.085 --> 09:37.553
You know, even if he's in advertising,

09:37.588 --> 09:38.554
Someone will want him.

09:39.054 --> 09:40.521
I just think it's so important

09:40.556 --> 09:42.507
That we be in control
of our own destinies.

09:42.542 --> 09:43.776
It doesn't matter.

09:43.811 --> 09:44.975
Marshall's a really good guy.

09:45.010 --> 09:47.012
He doesn't really care
about this kind of stuff.

09:47.047 --> 09:49.031
I can't believe it.

09:49.066 --> 09:50.981
Uh, excuse me...

09:51.016 --> 09:52.517
has anyone ever told
you you look just like

09:53.018 --> 09:54.519
Kate Preston's brother rod?

09:54.554 --> 09:55.986
Who?

09:56.021 --> 09:58.023
Rod Preston. Do you know him?

09:58.058 --> 10:00.025
Uh, no.

10:00.525 --> 10:02.027
Have you ever noticed that
people who look just alike

10:02.062 --> 10:04.029
Never seem to know each other?

10:04.064 --> 10:05.530
Hunh.

10:07.532 --> 10:08.498
Hi.

10:08.533 --> 10:10.910
Hey. How've you been?

10:10.945 --> 10:13.288
Fine. How are you?

10:15.007 --> 10:16.506
He's really depressed.

10:16.541 --> 10:19.043
God, isn't this place great?

10:19.078 --> 10:21.313
It's fantastic! I love it.

10:21.348 --> 10:23.548
I really like this song.

10:23.583 --> 10:25.015
Yeah.

10:25.050 --> 10:27.552
Do you like to dance?

10:27.587 --> 10:29.071
W- W-Would
you?

10:29.106 --> 10:30.331
Sure. Great.

10:30.366 --> 10:31.521
Shall we all go?

10:31.556 --> 10:34.559
I... I think he's
too depressed to dance.

10:34.594 --> 10:36.561
Hey, Jimmy, we're
going to dance... Come on.

10:36.596 --> 10:38.063
I'm too depressed to dance.

10:38.098 --> 10:39.147
Go ahead.

10:46.071 --> 10:47.537
What's wrong?

10:47.572 --> 10:49.574
Absolute disaster.

10:49.609 --> 10:50.540
What?

10:50.575 --> 10:52.327
I had to get some clients into the club,

10:52.362 --> 10:54.079
So I gave the boss
my coat to wear...

10:54.579 --> 10:56.081
"Here, wear this."

10:56.581 --> 10:58.548
It's really stupid.

10:58.583 --> 11:00.085
I can't believe what an idiot I am.

11:00.120 --> 11:02.552
Why? Your coat's nice.

11:02.587 --> 11:04.088
Well, that's just it: It is nice.

11:04.123 --> 11:05.590
But this guy's...
Marshall's...

11:05.625 --> 11:07.092
Clothes are hideous.

11:07.127 --> 11:08.558
It's famous.

11:08.593 --> 11:11.096
But to give him my
coat to put over them...

11:11.596 --> 11:12.597
It's so stupid.

11:13.098 --> 11:14.599
It's just really stupid.

11:14.634 --> 11:16.566
It's not stupid.

11:16.601 --> 11:18.103
This club's really hard to get into.

11:18.603 --> 11:21.071
It was unbelievably, incredibly dumb.

11:21.106 --> 11:23.608
He's a really nice
guy, and I insulted him.

11:23.643 --> 11:25.610
This nice guy that I stupidly insulted

11:25.645 --> 11:26.611
Is basically my boss.

11:27.112 --> 11:30.082
God, it was really stupid.

11:30.117 --> 11:32.368
Guess you're right.

11:32.403 --> 11:34.619
It was pretty stupid.

11:39.624 --> 11:42.627
Uh, can I get you a drink?

11:42.662 --> 11:44.594
Yeah, thanks.

11:44.629 --> 11:45.630
♪♪ If we lose our love ♪♪

11:45.665 --> 11:47.097
♪♪ It's a shame ♪♪

11:47.132 --> 11:49.384
♪♪ Ooh, wouldn't want ♪♪

11:49.419 --> 11:51.636
♪♪ To live with the pain ♪♪

11:51.671 --> 11:53.147
♪♪ Gonna take it ♪♪

11:53.182 --> 11:54.623
♪♪ Every night ♪♪

11:55.123 --> 11:57.626
Des, you're a wonderful man.

12:10.138 --> 12:12.641
Take care of yourself, des.

12:32.160 --> 12:34.628
Ok, van, what's up?

12:34.663 --> 12:36.665
Keep that ad guy friend
of yours out of here.

12:37.165 --> 12:37.666
Hi!

12:38.166 --> 12:39.167
What do you mean?

12:40.669 --> 12:42.170
When I turned him away
with a group of his clients,

12:42.205 --> 12:45.173
He snuck around back,
where you let them in.

12:45.208 --> 12:47.175
I didn't let 'em in.

12:47.642 --> 12:48.910
They're inside.

12:48.945 --> 12:50.178
Rick just saw them.

12:50.512 --> 12:51.645
Is this really important?

12:51.680 --> 12:53.181
I'm not out here on jerk patrol

12:53.682 --> 12:55.934
So you can let them in the back way.

12:55.969 --> 12:58.186
Bernie promised me he'd fire you

12:58.221 --> 12:59.688
If that guy's in the club.

12:59.723 --> 13:00.654
I can't believe that.

13:00.689 --> 13:02.441
You made Bernie promise to fire me?

13:05.694 --> 13:08.747
You really think Bernie
keeps his promises?

13:13.201 --> 13:15.704
♪♪ Aw, freakout ♪♪

13:15.739 --> 13:16.972
♪♪ Lefreak ♪♪

13:17.007 --> 13:18.357
♪♪ Tres chic ♪♪

13:18.392 --> 13:19.708
♪♪ Freakout ♪♪

13:21.209 --> 13:23.211
♪♪ Aw, freakout ♪♪

13:23.246 --> 13:24.480
♪♪ Lefreak ♪♪

13:24.515 --> 13:25.679
♪♪ Tres chic ♪♪

13:25.714 --> 13:26.965
I need to see Bernie.

13:27.000 --> 13:28.216
Bernie's not around.

13:28.383 --> 13:29.182
He's pretty mad, des.

13:29.217 --> 13:30.218
Van told him you were letting people

13:30.385 --> 13:31.685
In the back again.

13:31.720 --> 13:32.721
When you let people in the back,

13:32.756 --> 13:33.722
Is a cover being charged?

13:34.222 --> 13:35.188
Because that money
should be coming here.

13:35.223 --> 13:38.727
Of course we're not charging
a cover in the back. God!

13:38.762 --> 13:39.728
♪♪ Big fun ♪♪

13:40.228 --> 13:41.730
♪♪ To be had by everyone ♪♪

13:41.765 --> 13:43.697
♪♪ It's up to you ♪♪

13:43.732 --> 13:45.734
♪♪ Sure they can be done ♪♪

13:45.769 --> 13:47.701
Uh, Bernie...

13:47.736 --> 13:49.237
this thing that van's saying

13:49.272 --> 13:50.506
About your promising to fire me

13:50.541 --> 13:51.740
If Jimmy Steinway's in the club,

13:51.775 --> 13:53.206
That isn't true, is it?

13:53.241 --> 13:54.743
No, it's true. I can confirm that.

13:54.778 --> 13:55.744
This Jimmy Steinway,

13:56.244 --> 13:56.745
I don't want in the club.

13:57.245 --> 13:58.211
Why?

13:58.246 --> 14:01.214
Come here.

14:01.249 --> 14:05.218
♪♪ Aw, freakout ♪♪

14:05.253 --> 14:07.756
You promised to quit
letting friends in the back.

14:07.791 --> 14:09.257
No, you said we could
still let in people

14:09.292 --> 14:10.258
From the list.

14:10.392 --> 14:11.725
Don't contradict me, des.

14:11.760 --> 14:13.261
I don't want a lot of
ad people in the club,

14:13.762 --> 14:15.263
Particularly not this guy.

14:15.597 --> 14:16.730
Well, I didn't let him in.

14:16.765 --> 14:18.767
If van didn't either,
he's not in the club.

14:18.900 --> 14:20.268
Did I ever tell you that my first job

14:20.303 --> 14:22.235
Was in
advertising... At y&r?

14:22.270 --> 14:25.774
In those days, the big thing
was to be nice to everybody...

14:25.809 --> 14:28.276
To the secretaries, to
the "media department,"

14:28.311 --> 14:30.045
To the art director,
